The paper deals with the problem of gathering mobile robots, which is a classic problem in robotics and falls under the category of robot algorithms (cs.RO). The algorithm presented in the paper involves coordination and communication among the robots, which is a topic in distributed systems (cs.DS). The algorithm also involves graph theory and combinatorics, which are topics in discrete mathematics (cs.DC). The problem of gathering mobile robots is also relevant in the context of swarm robotics and multi-agent systems, which fall under the category of control and systems engineering (cs.SY). Finally, the paper presents a formal proof of correctness using the COQ proof assistant, which is a topic in logic and verification (cs.LO).
